  JOHANNESBURG - The Minister of Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development Thoko Didiza briefed the media to announce the outcome of the Agricultural Disaster Fund application process. Didiza said her department received 55,00 applications from farmers amid the lockdown. READ: SA to re-open agriculture sector, allow more manufacturing, retail About 15,000 applications have been approved and government will release about R500-million to the beneficiaries. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 